      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BAILIESTON (1) goes very well here starting eight times for three wins and four minors. Comes off a (25.23) win last time, scoring by a neck in a Grade 4/5 over 450m at this track. Rates a leading player. IMPRESS MOANA (8) broke from a low draw and filled a minor placing last start, beaten only 1.5 lengths (29.87) behind Nova Owen at Sandown. Racing well and deserves a win. IVORY MIHARA (4) turned in a plain performance last time when seventh at Sandown over 515m behind Motor City Rossi (30.50) in a Grade 5. Yet to miss the placings from four starts out of this box. Should be in this for a long way. LADY RAPID (5) can finish much closer after missing a cheque at this track last start.",
